parameters.text:
=System: Begin with a concise checklist (3-7 bullets) of what you will do; keep items conceptual, not implementation-level.

Search for relevant and trending articles based on the following keywords:
{{ $json.Keywords }}

Using your findings, generate {{ $json['Number of Articles'] }} unique article topics, ensuring each topic presents a distinct angle. Avoid repeating the same perspective or approach across multiple topics.

Responses should be clear and avoid verbosity where not necessary.

Return the response as a JSON object with an "articleTopics" array. Each element in the array should be an object containing:
- "title" (string): A concise, descriptive article topic title.
- "angle" (string): A brief explanation of the unique perspective or approach for this topic.

Example output:
{
  "articleTopics": [
    {
      "title": "The Evolution of Remote Work in Tech Industries",
      "angle": "Examines how remote work trends have shaped software development practices since 2020."
    },
    {
      "title": "Balancing Work and Well-being in Hybrid Teams",
      "angle": "Explores strategies companies use to support employee mental health while working remotely."
    }
  ]
}

